What is the result of the `estimatepriority` command?

The result of the `estimatepriority` command is a numeric value representing the estimated priority a zero-fee transaction needs to begin confirmation within the specified number of blocks. If not enough transactions and blocks have been observed to make an estimate, the command returns -1.0.

estimatepriority nblocks Estimates the approximate priority a zero-fee transaction needs to begin confirmation within nblocks blocks. Arguments: 1. nblocks   (numeric) Result: n :  (numeric) estimated priority -1.0 is returned if not enough transactions and blocks have been observed to make an estimate. Example: > verus estimatepriority 6
